<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>ServiceNet is Rackspace's term for their internal cloud network. Unlike traffic going through the public internet, bandwidth on this network - say between a web server and cloudfiles - is not charged.</p>

<p>Zend_Service_Rackspace_Abstract does not provide any way for the developer to say they want to use ServiceNet, so all traffic will be charged. There should be a setUseServiceNet() method or similar.</p>

